title: Link and Button Click Tracking Analysis
findings:
All click interactions are being tracked through Tag Manager including:
- Link clicks
- Navigation elements
- Button clicks
- Other clickable elements
observations:
1. The tracking implementation appears to be broad and comprehensive, capturing all click interactions
2. Current setup may be generating a large volume of event data
recommendations:
1. Audit and Prioritize Events:
- Review all tracked click events and identify which are actually needed for analysis
- Prioritize tracking of business-critical interactions
- Consider removing tracking from non-essential elements

2. Implement Event Categorization
- Create a clear event naming convention
- Organize events into logical categories (e.g., navigation, form interactions, content engagement)
- Add event labels to provide more context about the interaction
